people the wrong way

246
00:13:59,125 --> 00:14:01,166
that it started to look
like the old timer avatar

247
00:14:01,250 --> 00:14:03,500
was gonna have to call it quits.

248
00:14:03,583 --> 00:14:05,958
But he bounced back.

249
00:14:06,041 --> 00:14:07,916
You said he's not like that now?

250
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:12,458
Yep. He's back to his usual cool
and mellow self these days.

251
00:14:12,541 --> 00:14:15,291
He's gone on record
and publically apologized

252
00:14:15,375 --> 00:14:17,083
for his behavior.

253
00:14:17,166 --> 00:14:18,833
It's pretty tough
for an avatar who went

254
00:14:18,916 --> 00:14:22,666
into such a drastic decline to
make a full comeback, though.

255
00:14:24,791 --> 00:14:27,541
So are you doing an official
investigation into him?

256
00:14:27,625 --> 00:14:29,666
Did Talisman do something wrong?

257
00:14:29,750 --> 00:14:31,875
I can't really talk
about the details.

258
00:14:31,958 --> 00:14:34,791
It's complicated though we
need to physically track down

259
00:14:34,875 --> 00:14:35,958
and locate him.

260
00:14:36,041 --> 00:14:37,833
the person behind
the avatar, I mean.

261
00:14:37,916 --> 00:14:40,125
That's kind of intriguing.

262
00:14:40,208 --> 00:14:42,791
I'd be happy to offer
you some assistance.

263
00:14:42,875 --> 00:14:44,458
What?

264
00:14:44,541 --> 00:14:46,208
A PSB beaureacrat in debt

265
00:14:46,291 --> 00:14:49,333
to little ol' me could
come in handy.

266
00:14:49,416 --> 00:14:52,500
Infamous anarchist Spooky
Boogie working with the law.

267
00:14:52,583 --> 00:14:53,916
Wasn't expecting that.

268
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:56,708
That's just part of my
public persona and besides,

269
00:14:56,791 --> 00:14:59,833
we were classmates,
just leave this to me, okay?

270
00:15:03,416 --> 00:15:06,250
Your attention please,
my dear and loyal guests.

271
00:15:06,333 --> 00:15:08,458
To show my appreciation
for your support,

272
00:15:08,541 --> 00:15:10,750
for all your love, and
for visiting my forum,

273
00:15:10,833 --> 00:15:12,083
I'd like to invite you all

274
00:15:12,166 --> 00:15:14,583
to a modest yet grand
party held in your honor.

275
00:15:14,666 --> 00:15:17,125
It'll be a meetup in
Roppongi on the fourth.

276
00:15:17,208 --> 00:15:20,083
In addition, I will challenge
my friend Talisman to a duel.

277
00:15:20,166 --> 00:15:22,625
A chance to win the
White Crown I currently hold.

278
00:15:22,708 --> 00:15:25,416
I hope to see all of you there.

279
00:15:27,750 --> 00:15:28,791
A meet-up?

280
00:15:28,875 --> 00:15:30,916
That's right
CommuField users gather

281
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:32,875
somewhat regularly for parties.

282
00:15:32,958 --> 00:15:35,541
They wear Holo-Cosplay
that simulates their

283
00:15:35,625 --> 00:15:38,958
online social avatars
It's completely anonymous.

284
00:15:39,041 --> 00:15:41,916
The modern version
of a masquerade ball.

285
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,791
Alright, but the big question:

286
00:15:43,875 --> 00:15:46,666
How can we be certain that
Talisman will actually show up?

287
00:15:46,750 --> 00:15:49,291
He can't afford not to.

288
00:15:49,375 --> 00:15:52,000
His popularity will
plummet if he backs out.

289
00:15:52,083 --> 00:15:54,125
Whoever's been posing
as Hayama's avatar,

290
00:15:54,208 --> 00:15:56,166
they've got no
choice but to be there.

291
00:15:56,250 --> 00:15:57,458
They've already put
so much effort

292
00:15:57,541 --> 00:16:00,041
into making sure his
CommuField runs smoothly.

293
00:16:00,125 --> 00:16:01,875
They've gotta
show at this meet-up

294
00:16:01,958 --> 00:16:05,083
if they don't wanna squander all
the work they've put into it.

295
00:16:05,166 --> 00:16:07,375
He can't hide behind
his Holo-Cosplay.

296
00:16:07,458 --> 00:16:08,583
The only thing we have

297
00:16:08,666 --> 00:16:10,166
to do is get him in the
Dominator's sights

298
00:16:10,250 --> 00:16:12,916
and his Crime Coefficient
is bound to give him away.

299
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:14,666
Right. Where's the meet-up?

300
00:16:14,750 --> 00:16:18,125
At a club in Roppongi, Exoset.

301
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:21,250
Ginoza's team is on
the front entrance

302
00:16:21,333 --> 00:16:23,375
and the drones are
positioned out back.

303
00:16:23,458 --> 00:16:26,250
All we've gotta do is stand
back and wait for him to show.

304
00:16:27,541 --> 00:16:30,708
I take back that masquerade
ball comment I made earlier.

305
00:16:30,791 --> 00:16:32,500
It's a hell of a
lot weirder than that.

306
00:16:32,583 --> 00:16:34,666
They're packed like
cigarettes into a place

307
00:16:34,750 --> 00:16:36,541
with only two exits and
they don't even know

308
00:16:36,625 --> 00:16:38,208
who's standing next to them.

309
00:16:38,291 --> 00:16:39,875
How can they be
comfortable with this?

310
00:16:39,958 --> 00:16:42,125
It's impossible to participate
in the social networks

311
00:16:42,208 --> 00:16:44,541
if you're afraid of anonymity.

312
00:16:44,625 --> 00:16:46,375
But this isn't virtual.

313
00:16:46,458 --> 00:16:49,541
You can bleed and die in
here and any one of these

314
00:16:49,625 --> 00:16:52,125
costumed freaks could be
carrying a knife on them.

315
00:16:52,208 --> 00:16:53,875
And they're fine
with putting their lives

316
00:16:53,958 --> 00:16:55,500
into the hands of strangers.

317
00:16:55,583 --> 00:16:57,791
They're out of their
damn minds if you ask me.

318
00:16:57,875 --> 00:16:59,041
That kind of thinking is exactly

319
00:16:59,125 --> 00:17:02,416
what causes your
Pycho-Pass to get so cloudy.

320
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:05,166
Sorry, that was rude.
It came out the wrong way.

321
00:17:05,250 --> 00:17:08,166
It's okay.
That's a legitimate point.

322
00:17:08,250 --> 00:17:10,083
Take a look. It's him.

323
00:17:13,250 --> 00:17:16,208
We can't get a read from here
Too many guests to clearly aim.

324
00:17:16,291 --> 00:17:18,583
I'm gonna try to
get closer to him.

325
00:17:20,416 --> 00:17:23,375
Dominator Suppression
System Online.

326
00:17:36,250 --> 00:17:37,000
No way.

327
00:17:37,083 --> 00:17:38,666
Now would I lie to you?

328
00:17:41,083 --> 00:17:43,125
Well, crap I knew it.

329
00:17:48,250 --> 00:17:50,916
Mr. Mido? You were
right on the money.

330
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:53,583
A Dominator was just
detected out on the floor.

331
00:17:53,666 --> 00:17:56,666
There's definitely an
Inspector here. No doubt.

332
00:17:56,750 --> 00:17:59,958
So it really is a trap.
Damn Spooky Boogie.

333
00:18:00,041 --> 00:18:01,958
You better get out of
there while you can.

334
00:18:02,041 --> 00:18:04,833
It'll royally muck things
up if you get caught.

335
00:18:04,916 --> 00:18:06,208
I'm aware of that.

336
00:18:06,291 --> 00:18:08,416
I've also got
unfinished business.

337
00:18:08,500 --> 00:18:10,041
I'll help you get out.

338
00:18:40,541 --> 00:18:42,000
Shit! What the
hell just happened?

339
00:18:42,083 --> 00:18:44,916
Someone hacked all
the Holo-Cosplay!

340
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:46,625
The suspect's gonna run!

341
00:18:46,708 --> 00:18:48,416
Dammit! Pull your Dominator.

342
00:18:48,500 --> 00:18:51,291
We'll root him out by
his Crime Coefficient.

343
00:18:53,541 --> 00:18:55,166
It's the CID!

344
00:18:56,125 --> 00:18:56,958
Wait!

345
00:18:57,041 --> 00:18:59,250
Crime Coefficient Over one-ten.

346
00:18:59,333 --> 00:19:03,541
Over one-forty.
Target for enforcement action.

347
00:19:03,958 --> 00:19:05,541
Crap, how many of 'em are there?

348
00:19:05,625 --> 00:19:08,041
This went from covert
to full-blown raid.

349
00:19:10,958 --> 00:19:12,916
Well this is great.

350
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:14,333
They spotted us.

351
00:19:17,625 --> 00:19:19,458
Oh! Sorry!

352
00:19:24,750 --> 00:19:26,625
What the hell were you trying
to pull with this meet-up?

353
00:19:26,708 --> 00:19:29,708
My boyfriend got
busted by the MWPSB!

354
00:19:29,791 --> 00:19:31,458
Are you gonna pay
for his treatment?

355
00:19:31,541 --> 00:19:34,875
Please! Everyone just calm down!

356
00:19:34,958 --> 00:19:36,666
I had nothing
to do with this raid!

357
00:19:36,750 --> 00:19:39,125
I'm just as upset
about it as you are!

358
00:19:39,208 --> 00:19:42,833
We can see right through
your lies, Spooky Boogie.

359
00:19:42,916 --> 00:19:44,333
Judging by the way it went down

360
00:19:44,416 --> 00:19:46,875
they must've been in the club
before the party started.

361
00:19:46,958 --> 00:19:48,458
The only way that
could happen was

362
00:19:48,541 --> 00:19:50,583
if the organizer was in on it.

363
00:19:53,750 --> 00:19:56,416
You've always touted anarchism
as your guiding principle.

364
00:19:56,500 --> 00:19:59,250
One of the reasons so many
love you and yet you've colluded

365
00:19:59,333 --> 00:20:01,916
with the government
against your own followers.

366
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:03,833
A truly unacceptable offense.

367
00:20:03,916 --> 00:20:05,750
Wha- That is not true!

368
00:20:05,833 --> 00:20:07,000
From the way it looked to me,

369
00:20:07,083 --> 00:20:09,250
you're the one they
were after, Talisman.

370
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:11,625
So if anyone's at
fault here, it's you!

371
00:20:11,708 --> 00:20:15,500
You've betrayed your fans,
as well as your own character.

372
00:20:15,583 --> 00:20:18,625
You have no right to call
yourself Spooky Boogie

373
00:20:18,708 --> 00:20:20,666
and you certainly no
longer deserve the trust

374
00:20:20,750 --> 00:20:22,666
and adoration of our community.

375
00:20:22,750 --> 00:20:26,083
You... You have no right to say
that, you don't know anything!

376
00:20:26,166 --> 00:20:29,875
I know more about you than you
could ever know about yourself.

377
00:20:30,208 --> 00:20:32,541
Shut up, you creep!

378
00:20:32,625 --> 00:20:34,916
What's his problem?
Talk about creepy.

379
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:36,916
Just who the hell
does he think he is?

380
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:39,625
I'm putting a block on
his access to my CommuField.

381
00:20:39,708 --> 00:20:42,333
Screw that. He won't get
anywhere near me again.

382
00:20:42,416 --> 00:20:44,666
There's really no point in that.

383
00:20:48,041 --> 00:20:49,333
It's no longer your forum.

384
00:20:49,416 --> 00:20:52,583
And Spooky Boogie is no
longer your avatar, either.

385
00:21:05,291 --> 00:21:06,750
Did you kill her?

386
00:21:06,833 --> 00:21:09,958
This woman had no right to carry
on acting as Spooky Boogie.

387
00:21:10,041 --> 00:21:12,875
But Spooky Boogie shouldn't
vanish from the net.

388
00:21:12,958 --> 00:21:15,916
She puts a smile
on so many faces.

389
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:19,208
With a little bit of crowd work,
Spooky Boogie can still be used.

390
00:21:19,291 --> 00:21:21,666
The woman behind
her can be flushed.

391
00:21:21,750 --> 00:21:25,125
Sure, I bet you'll make
a great Spooky Boogie.

392
00:21:25,208 --> 00:21:28,375
Even better than
Shoko Sugawara herself.

393
00:21:28,458 --> 00:21:31,166
Just look at what
you've done with Talisman.

394
00:21:31,250 --> 00:21:32,833
You're leaps and bounds
better than Hayama.

